The paper deals with distributed computing in hypergraphs, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also focuses on fundamental problems such as Maximal Independent Set (MIS), coloring, maximal matching, and maximal clique, which are studied in Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Distributed Systems (cs.DS). The paper also presents applications of hypergraph MIS to solving problems in (standard) graphs, which falls under the category of Graph Theory (cs.GT) and Network Science (cs.NE).
